com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class UpdateMatchRecordRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianObjectRequest
        • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.UpdateMatchRecordRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RecordKeyProvider, SiperianObjectUidProvider, Serializable

    public class UpdateMatchRecordRequest
extends SiperianObjectRequest
implements SiperianObjectUidProvider, RecordKeyProvider
    Create or update a record in a match table.

    Required Parameters:

    • setRecordKey(RecordKey)
    • setMatchedRecordKey(RecordKey)

    Optional Parameters:

    • setAutomerge(boolean) - default false
    • setMatchReverse(boolean) - default false
    • setTaskId(String) - default null

    Usage Example: The following example flags 111 and 222 for automerge. 

    
 UpdateMatchRecordRequest request = new UpdateMatchRecordRequest();
 request.setMatchRuleUid(SiperianObjectType.MATCH_RULE.makeUid("MyMatchRule"));
 request.setUnmergedRecordKey(RecordKey.sourceKey("111", "Acme"));
 request.setMatchedRecordKey(RecordKey.sourceKey("222", "Acme"));
 UpdateMatchRecordResponse response = sipClient.process(request);
    See Also:
    UpdateMatchRecordResponse, Serialized Form

    API Pair: UpdateMatchRecordResponse

    API Group: Merge Workflow
